                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.Consultation(2)/279: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-12T22:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 12, 1940—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>189. Department’s circular telegram July 11, 5 p.m. Government project on same
                    topic is very brief but, according to Minister for Foreign Affairs, similar in
                    purpose to Department’s draft and contemplates trusteeship and two-thirds
                    vote.</p>
                <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs leaves for Habana Monday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Braden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
